Installing UIChat

1. cd to the directory where you downloaded the UICHat-<ver>.tar.gz file.
2. Untar the distribution :

	tar xvzf UIChat-<ver>.tar.gz
	
3. cd UIChat-<ver>
4. To install the program run : 

	sudo . ./install.sh
	
5. This will install all files to their proper places including :

	/etc/uichatd/uichatd.conf
	/etc/uichatd/uichatd.template
	/usr/local/share/doc/uichatd/UIChat_Syntax.pdf
	/usr/local/share/doc/uichatd/README.txt
	/usr/local/share/doc/uichatd/COPYING
	/usr/local/bin/uichat
	/usr/local/bin/uichatd
	
The install script will also create the /var/ax25/uichatd/heard file	
and set appropriate permissions where applicable.

NOTE: If you are doing an upgrade from a previous version, heard, uichatd.conf and
any .msg files will NOT be over-written.  You should check uichatd.conf againt
the latest uichatd.template file to note any changes to it's content or format.

6. To start uichat, simply enter :
	
	sudo uichat
	
and you will be met with a UICHAT> prompt.  Use ? <Enter> to get a help screen.

Please refer to /usr/share/doc/uichatd/UIChat_Syntax.pdf for syntax rules.

Questions may be directed to ab4mw@radcommsoft.com
